1. Write a script called mycase, using the case utility to checks the type of character
entered by a user:
a. Upper Case.
b. Lower Case.
c. Number.
---------------------------------------
#!/usr/bin/bash
shopt -s extglob
LC_COLLATE=C
echo "Enter a character:"
read c
case $c in
  [a-z]) echo "lowercase"
	  ;;
  [A-Z]) echo "uppercase"
	  ;;
  [0-9]) echo "number"
	  ;;
  "") echo "nothing"
	  ;;
  *) echo "special character"
	  ;;
esac
========================================================

d. Nothing.
2. Enhanced the previous script, by checking the type of string entered by a user:
a. Upper Cases.
b. Lower Cases.
c. Numbers.
d. Mix.
e. Nothing.
-------------------------------
#!/usr/bin/bash
shopt -s extglob
LC_COLLATE=C
echo enter your string
read c
case $c in
	+([a-z]))
		echo upper
		;;
	+([A-Z]))
		echo lower
		;;
	+([0-9]))
		echo number
		;;
	+([a-zA-Z0-9]))
		echo mix
		;;
	*)
		echo nothing
		;;
esac
